WEBVTT

01:07.192 --> 01:07.901
HOW WE DOING HERE, LOWELL?

01:09.110 --> 01:09.569
{\an1}DID YOU FIND
THE TROUBLE YET?

01:10.570 --> 01:11.279
WAS IT THE MAGNETO?

01:12.113 --> 01:13.490
UH-UH.

01:13.573 --> 01:14.616
IS FUEL INJECTOR CLOGGED?

01:14.699 --> 01:16.326
UH-UH.

01:16.409 --> 01:18.119
DO YOU HAVE ANY IDEA
WHAT THE PROBLEM IS?

01:18.203 --> 01:20.288
UH-HUH.

01:20.371 --> 01:21.331
WHAT IS IT?

01:21.414 --> 01:24.167
{\an1}YOU'RE STANDING
ON MY HAND.

01:24.250 --> 01:26.544
WHY DIDN'T YOU
SAY SOMETHING?

01:26.628 --> 01:27.796
{\an1}WELL, IT FELT
KIND OF GOOD AT FIRST.

01:29.255 --> 01:32.175
{\an1}TOOK MY MIND OFF
OF THIS MESS.

01:32.258 --> 01:34.886
{\an4}JOE, I DON'T KNOW
HOW LONG I CAN STALL THE
PASSENGERS .

01:34.969 --> 01:36.513
{\an1}THEY FINISHED ALL MY BUTTER
COOKIES

01:36.596 --> 01:39.015
AND HAVE CRAZED LOOKS
IN THEIR EYES.

01:39.098 --> 01:41.059
WELL IT LOOKS LIKE WE MIGHT HAVE
TO CANCEL THIS FLIGHT.

01:41.142 --> 01:43.311
ASK THEM TO
BE PATIENT.

01:43.394 --> 01:45.939
{\an4}OKAY WELL,WHEN CHEESE DOODLES
RUN OUT, IT'S EVERY MAN FOR
HIMSELF.

01:46.856 --> 01:47.440
WELL THAT'S A RELIEF.

01:48.566 --> 01:49.818
DID YOU FIND THE PROBLEM?

01:49.901 --> 01:51.903
{\an1}NO, BUT IT LOOKS AS IF
I CAN SAVE THIS FINGERNAIL.

01:54.155 --> 01:56.032
{\an1}MAY I PLEASE HAVE YOUR
ATTENTION?

01:56.115 --> 01:57.659
WE REGRET TO INFORM YOU

01:57.742 --> 02:00.495
{\an1}THAT SANDPIPER AIR FLIGHT 14
TO BOSTON

02:00.578 --> 02:03.748
HAS BEEN FURTHER DELAYED
DUE TO MECHANICAL DIFFICULTIES.

02:04.457 --> 02:05.875
(<i> grumbling</i> )

02:05.959 --> 02:07.544
BUT ON THE BRIGHT SIDE

02:07.627 --> 02:10.213
{\an1}FREEDOM AND DEMOCRACY
BROKE OUT IN EASTERN EUROPE.

02:12.257 --> 02:12.882
{\an3}AEROMASS FLIGHT 126
TO BOSTON

02:15.468 --> 02:17.220
{\an3}WILL BEGIN BOARDING
SHORTLY

02:17.303 --> 02:19.556
{\an4}AND THANK YOU FOR
CHOOSING THE AEROMASS. THE
AIRLINE

02:19.639 --> 02:23.184
{\an4}THAT BELIEVES IN ACTUALLY
TRANSPORTING PEOPLE FROM ONE
PLACE TO ANOTHER .

02:25.812 --> 02:27.105
HOW ABOUT A CUP OF COFFEE PRETTY
LADY ?

02:27.188 --> 02:29.399
COMING RIGHT UP.

02:29.482 --> 02:32.360
{\an5}SAY WHAT HAPPENED TO THAT FAT,
OLD GEEZER WHO USED TO RUN THIS
PLACE?

02:32.443 --> 02:33.111
WHAT WAS HIS NAME?

02:33.611 --> 02:35.113
DADDY?

02:36.155 --> 02:36.823
WHOOPS.

02:37.323 --> 02:38.741
STILL KNOW HOW

02:38.825 --> 02:40.159
TO TURN OFF
THE LADIES, HUH, McCOY?

02:41.744 --> 02:42.912
{\an1}-HACKETT!
-HEY!

02:42.996 --> 02:43.913
HEY YOU OLD PROP-WASH, YOU.

02:44.706 --> 02:45.540
HOW ARE YOU?

02:45.623 --> 02:48.084
{\an1}AH YOU KNOW ME ,STILL FLYING,
STILL LYING.

02:48.167 --> 02:50.420
HELEN CHAPPEL,
DANNY McCOY.

02:50.503 --> 02:53.715
{\an1}HI, HELEN, I'M GUESSING
YOU'RE A SAGITTARIUS.

02:53.798 --> 02:56.259
{\an3}I'M GUESSING YOU'RE
NO HIGH SCHOOL GRADUATE.

02:56.342 --> 02:57.427
HEY, BAIL OUT,
DANNY.

02:57.510 --> 02:58.595
ABOUT TO CRASH AND BURN.

02:58.678 --> 02:59.762
SO WHAT'S GOING ON WITH YOU GUY?

02:59.846 --> 03:01.014
{\an1}I'M FLYING FOR
AN AIR EXPRESS COMPANY NOW.

03:02.181 --> 03:02.932
HOW ABOUT YOU?

03:03.016 --> 03:04.559
AH, FLYING A HOT LITTLE CESSNA A
402 .

03:05.685 --> 03:06.853
GOT A LITTLE
COMMUTER OPERATION HERE...

03:08.104 --> 03:09.439
AHEM.

03:09.522 --> 03:11.649
{\an4}THAT MY BROTHER ACTUALLY
OWNS ,AND WAS KIND ENOUGH TO
GIVE ME A JOB ON.

03:11.733 --> 03:13.484
DANNY McCOY,THIS IS
MY BROTHER JOE.

03:13.568 --> 03:14.235
{\an1}-HI, JOE.
-HEY, DANNY HOW YOU DOING.

03:14.319 --> 03:15.612
{\an1}GREAT.

03:15.695 --> 03:17.572
BOY, SEEING YOU IS REALLY WIERD.

03:17.655 --> 03:19.115
A COUPLE OF WEEKS AGO
I WAS IN ST. CROIX

03:19.198 --> 03:20.575
AND I RAN INTO
YOUR EX-WIFE.

03:20.658 --> 03:22.994
{\an5}HOPE YOU WERE
IN YOUR CAR
AT THE TIME.

03:23.077 --> 03:23.870
SAW CAROL, HUH?

03:23.953 --> 03:26.247
YEAH,SHE LOOKED GREAT!

03:26.331 --> 03:27.498
HERE'S A NEWS
FLASH FOR YOU--

03:27.582 --> 03:29.959
REMEMBER THAT GUY
CAROL LEFT YOU FOR?

03:30.043 --> 03:30.460
UH, VAGUELY.

03:30.543 --> 03:32.128
SHE DUMPED HIM, TOO.

03:32.211 --> 03:34.255
REALLY? HOO-HOO.

03:34.339 --> 03:36.591
I CAN'T BELIEVE YOU'RE SO CALM--
THAT JERK STOLE YOUR WIFE.

03:36.674 --> 03:37.467
HEY MAN IT'S NO BIG DEAL,

03:37.550 --> 03:39.093
I MEAN I STOLE
CAROL FROM JOE

03:39.177 --> 03:41.262
{\an5}AND WE BOTH
LAUGH ABOUT IT
RIGHT JOE.

03:41.346 --> 03:42.931
HA-HA-HA-HA-HA.

03:43.014 --> 03:44.349
IT'S ALL ANCIENT HISTORY,

03:44.432 --> 03:47.101
{\an1}IT'S MERE FOOTNOTE IN THE
BOOK OF BRIAN HACKETT'S LIFE

03:47.185 --> 03:50.271
{\an4}"VASTLY ENTERTAINING VOLUME BY
THE WAY-- I JUST COULDN'T PUT
IT DOWN."

03:50.355 --> 03:51.481
SAYS JUDITH KRANTZ.

03:51.564 --> 03:55.610
{\an1}"I COULDN'T KEEP IT DOWN"
SAYS JOE HACKETT.

03:55.693 --> 03:58.613
{\an5}SPEAKING OF
THE DRY HEAVES,
HOW IS CAROL?

03:58.696 --> 04:01.115
{\an1}AM I SENSING
A CERTAIN HISTORY HERE?

04:01.199 --> 04:03.660
THAT WOMAN LIVED
TO HUMILIATE ME.

04:03.743 --> 04:05.536
{\an1}SHE DID A PRETTY
GOOD JOB ON THESE GUYS, TOO.

04:05.620 --> 04:06.704
WELL I'LL SAY ONE THING FOR HER,

04:06.788 --> 04:09.666
{\an1}SHE TAUGHT ME ONE OF
<i>THE</i> GREAT LESSONS IN LIFE--

04:09.749 --> 04:11.668
CHASING WOMEN
SURE BEATS CATCHING THEM.

04:11.751 --> 04:14.128
YEAH, YOU'RE BETTER OFF WITHOUT
CAROL.

04:14.212 --> 04:15.672
LET HER MOVE TO LONDON.

04:15.755 --> 04:16.339
{\an1}CAROL'S MOVING TO
LONDON?

04:16.422 --> 04:17.673
FIRST THE BLIST AND NOW THIS.

04:17.757 --> 04:20.009
{\an3}HAVEN'T THOSE PEOPLE
SUFFERED ENOUGH?

04:20.093 --> 04:22.637
SAID SHE GOT A JOB OVER THERE.

04:22.720 --> 04:24.013
SHE'S PACKING AND LEAVING THE
24th.

04:24.097 --> 04:26.683
THE 24th?
THAT'S-THAT'S TODAY.

04:26.766 --> 04:28.977
WELL I BETTER SHOVE OFF-- LOOKS
LIKE THE FOG'S ROLLING IN.

04:29.060 --> 04:29.519
TAKE IT EASY DANNY.

04:29.602 --> 04:31.020
HACKETT, I'LL CALL YOU.

04:31.104 --> 04:33.523
{\an1}-WE'LL RAISE SOME HELL.
- YOU BETCHA

04:33.606 --> 04:35.233
{\an1}LISTEN BABE, SORRY ABOUT THAT
CRACK ABOUT YOUR FATHER.

04:35.316 --> 04:38.486
{\an4}YEAH,FOR A MOMENT THERE, I
THOUGHT WE WERE GONNA GROW OLD
TOGETHER.

04:38.569 --> 04:40.738
BUT YOU GREW OLD
REAL QUICK.

04:40.822 --> 04:46.202
OOH... SNAG!

04:46.286 --> 04:49.706
{\an5}OH WHAT DO YOU KNOW,ANOTHER GUY
GROUND TO DUST BY THE
CAROL-MACHINE.

04:49.789 --> 04:52.375
YEAH,WE'RE LUCKY TO BE
RID OF THAT WOMAN.

04:52.458 --> 04:53.418
{\an1}YEAH LET HER GO OFF
TO ENGLAND TO WREAK HAVOC

04:53.501 --> 04:55.211
ON THE MEN
OF THE BRITISH EMPIRE.

04:55.294 --> 04:56.379
BOY, IS SHE GOING
TO BE DISAPPOINTED

04:56.462 --> 05:02.218
WHEN SHE FINDS OUT
BIG BEN IS A CLOCK.

05:02.301 --> 05:04.053
SURE YOU'RE OKAY?

05:04.137 --> 05:06.514
OKAY? I'M GREAT.

05:06.597 --> 05:08.558
{\an4}WHY WOULDN'T
I--THE WOMAN MEANS
NOTHING TO ME.

05:08.641 --> 05:11.060
I CAN'T EVEN REMEMBER
WHAT HER FACE LOOKS LIKE.

05:11.144 --> 05:17.859
{\an1}I'M GOING TO SIT HERE QUIETLY
AND FORGET THE REST OF HER.

05:17.942 --> 05:28.411
(<i> sighs</i> )

05:28.494 --> 05:29.871
BREN,WHAT ARE YOU DOING?

05:29.954 --> 05:31.914
{\an1}TRYING TO GET A LITTLE
INFORMATION ON A PASSENGER

05:31.998 --> 05:32.915
WHO'S FLYING TO LONDON.

05:32.999 --> 05:34.292
THAT'S AGAINST
REGULATIONS.

05:34.375 --> 05:36.586
FAY, THIS IS LOVE.

05:36.669 --> 05:38.463
WELL,I LOVE YOU, TOO,
BUT RULES ARE RULES.

05:38.546 --> 05:40.089
NO YOU DON'T UNDERSTAND FAY.

05:40.173 --> 05:42.050
I'VE GOT TO GET IN TOUCH
WITH CAROL.

05:42.133 --> 05:46.262
{\an1}THIS MIGHT BE MY LAST CHANCE
TO WIN HER BACK.

05:46.346 --> 05:47.597
AH! HERE SHE IS.

05:47.680 --> 05:49.432
YOU'RE A NAUGHTY BOY.

05:49.515 --> 05:52.101
OWWW, THERE. YOU HAPPY?

05:52.185 --> 05:53.019
OH LOOK AT THAT FAY.

05:53.102 --> 05:56.606
{\an1}CAROL HACKETT--
ST. CROIX TO MIAMI, MIAMI...

05:56.689 --> 05:59.275
MY GOD,OH MY GOD,SHE'S GOT A
FOUR-HOUR LAYOVER IN BOSTON.

05:59.358 --> 06:00.401
DO YOU KNOW WHAT THAT MEANS?

06:00.485 --> 06:02.612
{\an1}YES,HER TRAVEL AGENT SHOULD BE
FLOGGED.

06:02.695 --> 06:05.448
NO, NO, THIS IS
A SIGN, A SIGNAL

06:05.531 --> 06:08.117
THAT SHE WANTS ME
TO CONTACT HER

06:08.201 --> 06:10.995
{\an4}SO I'M GOING TO LEAVE
A MESSAGE AT THE GATE IN
BOSTON FOR HER .

06:11.079 --> 06:12.413
HELLO?

06:12.497 --> 06:13.247
YES, I WANT TO LEAVE A MESSAGE

06:13.331 --> 06:16.667
FOR A PASSENGER ARRIVING
FROM MIAMI.

06:16.751 --> 06:19.921
{\an1}YES THAT'S RIGHT,HER NAME IS
CAROL HACKETT.

06:20.004 --> 06:21.923
YES, THE MESSAGE IS

06:22.006 --> 06:25.343
"MEET ME AT THE TOP OF
THE PRUDENTIAL BUILDING

06:25.426 --> 06:28.012
"TONIGHT, 8:00.

06:28.096 --> 06:32.475
I'LL BE THERE. BRIAN."

06:32.558 --> 06:33.976
YES, TOP OF THE PRU.

06:34.060 --> 06:36.145
RIGHT... THANKS.

06:36.229 --> 06:38.981
OH! MAN.

06:39.065 --> 06:40.650
WHAT'S GOING ON?

06:40.733 --> 06:42.652
{\an1}HEY, GREAT NEWS, JOE. GREAT
NEWS.

06:42.735 --> 06:45.321
{\an1}CAROL IS STOPPING IN BOSTON
ON HER WAY TO LONDON.

06:45.404 --> 06:46.989
WHAT?

06:47.073 --> 06:48.491
{\an1}HAH YEAH,IT'S STARTING TO
ALL FIT TOGETHER HUH,

06:48.574 --> 06:50.493
{\an1}SUBCONSCIOUSLY, SHE'S HOPING
SHE'LL BUMP INTO ME.

06:50.576 --> 06:52.453
ARE YOU OUT OF YOUR MIND.

06:52.537 --> 06:54.372
{\an3}FIVE MINUTES AGO,
WE AGREED SHE WAS POISON.

06:54.455 --> 06:57.291
{\an4}YEAH BUT,THAT WAS THE OLD
CAROL-- SHE'S CHANGED SINCE
THEN.

06:57.375 --> 06:58.960
{\an1}BRIAN THIS IS A REALLY
STUPID IDEA.

06:59.043 --> 07:01.337
IT IS NOT STUPID.

07:01.420 --> 07:02.463
{\an1}YOUR THE GUY WHO SITS IN THE
PARK AND LETS PIGEONS

07:02.547 --> 07:04.674
EAT POPCORN
OUT OF HIS MOUTH

07:04.757 --> 07:07.510
{\an1}WELL EVEN HE'D
THINK IT'S A STUPID IDEA.

07:07.593 --> 07:09.846
{\an1}NOW ASSUMING I BUY ANY OF THIS
FOR A SECOND WHICH I DON'T,

07:09.929 --> 07:10.763
{\an1}WHY ARE YOU GOING
TO THE PRUDENTIAL BUILDING?

07:10.847 --> 07:12.014
{\an1}WHY DON'T YOU JUST MEET HER
AT THE AIRPORT?

07:12.098 --> 07:15.059
SHE'S GOT TO MAKE AN EFFORT TO.I
DON'T WANT TO SEEM DESPERATE.

07:15.143 --> 07:17.520
NO CHANCE OF THAT.

07:17.603 --> 07:20.982
{\an1}YES, YES, YES--
I SEE WHAT'S HAPPENING HERE.

07:21.065 --> 07:22.525
I SEE.

07:22.608 --> 07:24.861
{\an5}YOU WERE FEELING
A LITTLE JEALOUS OF CAROL AND I
GETTING BACK TOGETHER, HUH?

07:24.944 --> 07:26.320
ARE YOU KIDDING? I AM OVER HER,

07:26.404 --> 07:27.113
{\an3}I NEVER WANT
TO SEE HER AGAIN

07:27.196 --> 07:29.782
AS LONG AS I LIVE
AND THEN SOME.

07:29.866 --> 07:32.243
{\an4}SEE IT YOURSELF BUDDY BUT IF I
DON'T GET OUT OF HERE IN 45
MINUTES I'LL NEVER MAKE IT.

07:32.326 --> 07:33.578
{\an1}WE'VE GOT TO GET FLIGHT IN THE
AIR.

07:33.661 --> 07:35.371
{\an1}WAIT BRIAN,AREN'T YOU
FORGETTING?

07:35.454 --> 07:37.039
THE PLANE IS BROKEN.

07:37.123 --> 07:40.001
OH, NO, NO! AH!

07:40.084 --> 07:41.878
{\an1}WELL,LOWELL WILL TAKE CARE OF
IT.

07:41.961 --> 07:43.045
RIGHT LOWELL'S A GREAT MECHANIC.

07:43.129 --> 07:45.381
LOWELL CAN FIX ANYTHING.

07:45.464 --> 07:46.507
WILL SOMEBODY GIVE ME A HAND?

07:46.591 --> 07:48.593
MY SHIRT'S CAUGHT IN MY ZIPPER.

07:58.144 --> 07:59.812
LOWELL SURE MOVES SLOW

07:59.896 --> 08:02.732
{\an1}FOR SOMEONE WHO DOESN'T
BELONG TO A UNION.

08:02.815 --> 08:04.942
{\an4}ID I'M NOT OUT OF HERE IN 10
MINUTES, I'M GOING TO MISS
CAROL.

08:05.026 --> 08:07.236
{\an1}AH KID, YOU GOT
WHAT'S COMING TO YOU.

08:07.320 --> 08:09.405
{\an5}SHE WOULDN'T HAVE WALKED OUT IN
THE FIRST PLACE IF YOU'D
PERFORMED

08:09.488 --> 08:13.242
{\an1}YOUR HUSBANDLY DUTIES WITH
ANY DEGREE OF COMPETENTENCE.

08:13.326 --> 08:14.243
THIS FROM A MAN

08:14.327 --> 08:17.914
WHO RENTS RELATIONSHIPS
FROM A VIDEO STORE.

08:17.997 --> 08:20.249
{\an4}OH, MAN, I GOT TO
GET OUT OF HERE.GOT TO GET OUT
OF HERE.

08:20.333 --> 08:21.417
{\an1}I'M NOT GOING TO
MAKE IT.

08:21.500 --> 08:23.211
I GOT TO GO, I GOT TO GO.

08:23.294 --> 08:24.420
NOW, BRIAN. BRIAN.

08:24.503 --> 08:26.088
NO.DON'T BE SO IMPATIENT.

08:26.172 --> 08:27.798
YOU'VE GOT TO RELAX

08:27.882 --> 08:30.092
{\an3}LEARN TO LIVE
IN THE HERE AND NOW.

08:30.176 --> 08:32.886
{\an1}LISTEN TO ME, I REMEMBER ONCE
WHEN I WAS A STEWARDESS

08:32.970 --> 08:35.472
WE WERE SNOWBOUND
IN BUTTE, MONTANA

08:35.556 --> 08:37.558
WITHOUT ANY MONEY
OR CHANGE OF CLOTHES.

08:37.642 --> 08:40.937
BUT I DIDN'T CRY INT O MY BEER,
NO,I MADE THE BEST OF IT.

08:41.020 --> 08:42.772
I MET THREE NEW FRIENDS

08:42.855 --> 08:46.067
{\an3}I WOVE A BASKET
OUT OF AN OLD LAWN CHAIR

08:46.150 --> 08:50.446
AND I BECAME
AN HONORARY SIOUX INDIAN.

08:50.529 --> 08:52.573
HAVEN'T YOU EVER HAD
A BAD DAY?

08:52.657 --> 08:54.575
UH, NO, NOT YET

08:54.659 --> 08:59.455
BUT I BET YOU'LL
BE THERE WHEN I DO.

08:59.538 --> 09:01.290
OH TELL ME YOU
GOT GOOD NEWS.

09:01.374 --> 09:04.001
OKAY, FINALLYI GOT LOWELL'S
SHIRT OUT OF HIS ZIPPER.

09:04.085 --> 09:06.128
NO, NO-- THE PLANE.

09:06.212 --> 09:08.339
SORRY CHEIF,WERE GONNA HAVE TO
CANCEL OUR LAST FLIGHT.

09:08.422 --> 09:09.590
NO.NO. NO, HOW AM I GOING TO
SEE CAROL?

09:09.674 --> 09:12.969
{\an1}IF YOU ASK ME,
IT'S ALL FOR THE BEST.

09:13.052 --> 09:17.807
JOE,JOE YOU ALWAYS SAY,
"IT'S ALL FOR THE BEST."

09:17.890 --> 09:20.434
{\an1}HOW CAN EVERYTHING
ALWAYS BE FOR THE BEST?

09:20.518 --> 09:21.769
{\an1}WHEN THE PATRIOTS LOST
THE SUPER BOWL.

09:21.852 --> 09:23.312
{\an1}YOU SAID "IT'S ALL
FOR THE BEST."

09:23.396 --> 09:26.315
WHEN AUNT FERN BROKE HER HIP
WELL IT'S ALL FOR THE BEST?

09:26.399 --> 09:27.525
IS EVERYTHING FOR THE BEST?

09:27.608 --> 09:29.485
{\an1}IS THE HOLE IN THE OZONE
FOR THE BEST?

09:29.568 --> 09:30.611
WELL IT HAS MADE US MORE AWARE

09:30.695 --> 09:32.405
OF THE ENVIRONMENT.

09:32.488 --> 09:34.323
ANNOUNCING FINAL BOARDING

09:34.407 --> 09:38.661
FOR AEROMASS FLIGHT 160
TO BOSTON.

09:38.744 --> 09:43.332
HEY, ROY, HOW ABOUT GETTING ME
ON THE NEXT FLIGHT TO BOSTON?

09:43.416 --> 09:44.542
{\an1}I THOUGHT YOU SAID
YOU'D DIE

09:44.625 --> 09:45.668
BEFORE YOU TOOK
ONE OF MY FLIGHTS.

09:45.751 --> 09:48.671
{\an3}NO,I SAID I'D DIE
<i>ON</i> ONE OF YOUR FLIGHTS.

09:48.754 --> 09:50.298
{\an1}BUT THAT'S AN OLD STORY,
JUST GET ME A TICKET.

09:50.381 --> 09:53.843
{\an1}LET ME CHECK AND SEE
IF YOU HAVE A RESERVATION.

09:53.926 --> 09:56.178
WISENHEIMER...
WISENHEIMER...

09:56.262 --> 10:00.141
{\an1}I DON'T SEEM TO HAVE YOU HERE,
MR. L. MOUTH WISENHEIMER.

10:00.224 --> 10:03.311
{\an4}HERE TAKE ALL MY
WALLET TAKE ALL THE CASH,TAKE
THE CREDIT CARDS

10:03.394 --> 10:04.854
TAKE IT ALL--
JUST GET ME A TICKET.

10:04.937 --> 10:06.856
SORRY, I'M BOOKED SOLID.

10:06.939 --> 10:10.860
{\an1}IT'S ALL THAT OVERFLOW
BUSINESS FROM SANDPIPER.

10:10.943 --> 10:17.533
OH, I LOVE IRONY.

10:17.616 --> 10:19.327
THAT'S IT.

10:19.410 --> 10:20.161
IT'S OVER.

10:20.244 --> 10:21.412
I'M DOOMED.

10:21.495 --> 10:22.371
EVERYTHING BAD

10:22.455 --> 10:24.123
IN THE WORLD HAPPENS TO ME.

10:24.206 --> 10:26.375
PLANE'S FIXED.

10:26.459 --> 10:27.126
{\an1}SEE THAT'S IT ALL YOU
HAVE TO DO

10:27.209 --> 10:29.545
IS KEEP
A POSITIVE ATTITUDE...

10:29.628 --> 10:30.713
{\an1}ALRIGHT,WE CAN GET OUR LAST
FLIGHT TO BOSTON.

10:30.796 --> 10:32.757
{\an1}IT'S A MIRACLE, IT'S DIVINE
INTERVENTION.

10:32.840 --> 10:37.261
{\an4}IT'S A SIGN FROM GOD THAT HE
WANTS CAROL AND ME TO BE
TOGETHER.

10:37.345 --> 10:38.721
I JUST HEARD FROM
THE MAN UPSTAIRS.

10:38.804 --> 10:41.182
YOU JUST TALKED TO
THE MAN UPSTAIRS?

10:41.265 --> 10:43.351
YEAH-- FRANK.

10:43.434 --> 10:47.104
GOD'S NAME IS FRANK?

10:47.188 --> 10:48.397
NO, YOU SEE...

10:48.481 --> 10:49.565
YES, THAT'S RIGHT LOEWLL.

10:49.649 --> 10:51.567
WHAT? WHAT?

10:51.650 --> 10:53.235
WHAT DID HE SAY?

10:53.319 --> 10:54.570
WE'RE FOGGED IN.

10:54.653 --> 10:55.571
THE AIRPORT'S SHUT DOWN.

10:55.654 --> 10:56.906
OH, GOD.

10:56.989 --> 10:59.200
OH, GOD! OH, GOD!

10:59.283 --> 11:01.077
DON'T BE SO FORMAL.

11:01.160 --> 11:03.204
CALL HIM FRANK.

11:12.797 --> 11:14.256
COME ON, BRIAN.

11:14.340 --> 11:16.926
SIT DOWN RIGHT HERE
AND RELAX.

11:17.009 --> 11:19.929
YOU GAVE IT
YOUR BEST SHOT.

11:20.012 --> 11:24.934
YOU THOUGHT OF EVERYTHING
SHORT OF SWIMMING.

11:25.017 --> 11:27.436
{\an3}YOU'VE GOT TO FORGET
ABOUT HER.

11:27.520 --> 11:28.979
YOU DON'T UNDERSTAND JOE.

11:29.063 --> 11:32.441
{\an1}DO YOU KNOW HOW IT FEELS
TO LOSE A WOMAN LIKE THAT?

11:32.525 --> 11:35.236
NO,I KNOW HOW IT FEELS
TO LOSE THAT EXACT WOMAN.

11:35.319 --> 11:37.988
OH YEAH RIGHT ,THEN YOU, OF ALL
PEOPLE

11:38.072 --> 11:39.115
{\an1}SHOULD KNOW WHAT
I'M TALKING ABOUT.

11:39.198 --> 11:41.575
{\an1}I DON'T WANT TO BLOW IT
THIS TIME.

11:41.659 --> 11:44.453
BRIAN,YOU'VE GOT TO
TRUST ME, SHE'S NO GOOD FOR YOU.

11:44.537 --> 11:47.164
{\an1}WELL, SEE, THAT'S
THE CRAZY PART.

11:47.248 --> 11:48.833
I KNOW WHAT KIND
OF WOMAN SHE IS.

11:48.916 --> 11:50.960
I STILL WANT HER.

11:51.043 --> 11:52.795
KIND OF PATHETIC, HUH?

11:52.878 --> 11:54.797
WHAT'S EVEN MORE
PATHETIC

11:54.880 --> 11:57.800
{\an4}IS THAT YOU DREAMED UP
THIS WHOLE CRAZY ROMANTIC
SCENARIO IN YOUR HEAD.

11:57.883 --> 12:00.469
{\an5}DID YOU REALLY THINK SHE WAS
GOING TO MEET YOU ON THE TOP OF
A BUILDING

12:00.553 --> 12:03.639
LIKE IN SOME
CORNY MOVIE?

12:03.722 --> 12:06.809
{\an1}YOU REALLY DON'T THINK SHE'S
GOING TO SHOW UP, DO YOU?

12:06.892 --> 12:08.811
LET IT GO, BRIAN.

12:08.894 --> 12:12.273
YEAH.

12:12.356 --> 12:16.944
MAYBE YOU'RE RIGHT.

12:17.027 --> 12:21.824
{\an4}HEY JOE, I THINK I NEED
TO BE ALONE FOR A FEW MINUTES
OKAY.

12:21.907 --> 12:25.828
OKAY, I UNDERSTAND.

12:25.911 --> 12:27.538
AND BRIAN...

12:27.621 --> 12:32.168
JOE... PLEASE DON'T SAY
IT'S ALL FOR THE BEST.

12:32.251 --> 12:38.007
OKAY.

12:38.090 --> 12:40.551
{\an1}ROY: SIR YOU SEE,TAKING OFF IS
OUT OF THE QUESTION.

12:40.634 --> 12:42.845
{\an1}LOOK, I'VE GOT AN IMPORTANT
MEETING TO GET TO IN NEW YORK.

12:42.928 --> 12:44.388
IT'S A MATTER OF SAFETY SIR.

12:44.472 --> 12:48.225
{\an1}OKAY,OKAY, I HEAR
WHAT YOU'RE SAYING.

12:48.309 --> 12:53.355
{\an1}HOW MUCH WILL IT TAKE
TO MAKE THIS FOG GO AWAY?

12:53.439 --> 12:54.982
$100?

12:55.065 --> 12:55.524
{\an1}SIR THERE'S REALLY NOTHING
THAT'LL....

12:55.608 --> 12:57.234
$200?

12:57.318 --> 12:58.402
{\an1}SIR, YOU SEE THERE'S NOTHING
THAT I CAN...

12:58.486 --> 12:59.987
$500?

13:00.070 --> 13:02.823
THAT'S "ROY BIGGINS".

13:02.907 --> 13:04.825
TWO "G'S".

13:04.909 --> 13:10.539
I'LL DO WHAT I CAN.

13:10.623 --> 13:11.207
{\an3}JOE, AS LONG
AS WE'RE DELAYED

13:11.290 --> 13:13.042
I'D BE HAPPY
TO ORGANIZE

13:13.125 --> 13:15.461
THOSE FLIGHT MANIFESTS
FOR YOU.

13:15.544 --> 13:15.961
OH REALLY, FAY?

13:16.045 --> 13:17.421
THOSE ARE SO BORING.

13:17.505 --> 13:18.297
I DON'T MIND.

13:18.380 --> 13:22.676
ALL I'M DOING NOW
IS TALKING TO YOU.

13:22.760 --> 13:27.014
I'LL GET THEM.

13:27.097 --> 13:29.391
BRIAN, I KNOW YOU
WANT TO BE ALONE

13:29.475 --> 13:32.102
BUT COULD YOU HAND ME
THAT CLIPBOARD?

13:32.186 --> 13:35.022
IT'S THE SECOND ONE
FROM THE LEFT.

13:35.105 --> 13:37.566
LOOK, BRIAN, I KNOW
YOU'RE UPSET, BUT...

13:37.650 --> 13:38.567
LOWELL?

13:38.651 --> 13:40.569
WHAT ARE YOU DOING HERE?

13:40.653 --> 13:41.529
BRIAN PAID ME $20

13:41.612 --> 13:45.574
TO SIT IN THIS CHAIR
AND NOT SAY A WORD.

13:45.658 --> 13:48.744
OOPS.

13:48.827 --> 13:50.913
WHERE IS BRIAN?

13:50.996 --> 13:52.540
(<i> PLANE TAKING OFF</i> )

13:52.623 --> 13:54.917
OH, NO!

13:55.000 --> 13:56.585
I DON'T
BELIEVE IT.

13:56.669 --> 13:58.754
SOMEBODY IS TAKING OFF
IN THIS SOUP.

13:58.837 --> 14:00.130
MY IDIOT BROTHER.

14:00.214 --> 14:00.923
OH, BRIAN!

14:01.006 --> 14:02.633
ISN'T THAT ROMANTIC?

14:02.716 --> 14:04.760
WINGING HIS WAY THROUGH THE FOG

14:04.843 --> 14:08.222
{\an1}HASTENING TO THE BOSOM
OF THE WOMAN OF HIS DREAMS.

14:08.305 --> 14:09.056
THAT REMINDS ME.

14:09.139 --> 14:10.724
I'VE GOT TO STOP BY
THE VIDEO STORE

14:10.808 --> 14:16.438
ON THE WAY HOME.

14:16.522 --> 14:20.234
{\an1}WHEW, I DON'T EVER REMEMBER
A FOG LIKE THIS ONE.

14:20.317 --> 14:23.279
{\an3}THIS IS PRETTY THICK
ALL RIGHT, ROY

14:23.362 --> 14:25.948
BUT IT'S NOT WHAT
I'D CALL A GREAT FOG.

14:26.031 --> 14:28.576
{\an3}I'VE BEEN IN
SOME GREAT ONES.

14:28.659 --> 14:32.788
NOVEMBER ‘82--
GREAT FOG.

14:32.871 --> 14:36.750
APRIL ‘84--
GREAT FOG.

14:36.834 --> 14:38.502
JULY, ‘87...

14:38.586 --> 14:39.587
LET ME GUESS.

14:39.670 --> 14:40.879
GREAT FOG.

14:40.963 --> 14:44.675
{\an3}NO, BUT THE NEXT MONTH--
GREAT FOG.

14:44.758 --> 14:47.177
{\an1}LOGAN TOWER SAYS
BRIAN JUST LANDED IN BOSTON.

14:47.261 --> 14:48.971
{\an1}WHEW,THIS IS
THE STUPIDEST THING

14:49.054 --> 14:50.347
BRIAN HAS EVER DONE.

14:50.431 --> 14:53.809
{\an3}AND HE ONCE
PAINTED ME BLUE.

14:53.892 --> 14:55.519
{\an1}AS I RECALL,YOU DID SOME
FOOLISH THINGS

14:55.603 --> 14:56.812
{\an1}WHEN <i> YOU</i> WERE CHASING
AFTER CAROL.

14:56.895 --> 14:57.980
{\an1}ME?

14:58.063 --> 15:01.984
{\an4}HOW ABOUT WALKING YOUR DOG
AROUND HER BLOCK
FOR SIX HOURS

15:02.067 --> 15:04.778
{\an4}JUST SO YOU COULD
CASUALLY RUN INTO HER AS SHE
LEFT HER HOME.

15:04.862 --> 15:06.655
OH, YEAH-- THE LAST
COUPLE OF HOURS

15:06.739 --> 15:09.617
I HAD TO CARRY RANGER
ON MY SHOULDERS.

15:09.700 --> 15:13.287
{\an4}GOOD NEWS FOLKS,THE FOG IS
LIFTING, AND AEROMASS FLIGHT
160--

15:13.370 --> 15:15.497
COMFORT SERVICE TO BOSTON--

15:15.581 --> 15:19.460
WILL BE BOARDING MOMENTARILY.

15:19.543 --> 15:20.836
WELL,I GOT TO GO.

15:20.919 --> 15:21.962
WHERE ARE YOU GOING?

15:22.046 --> 15:23.672
TO FULLFILL MY MISSIN GIN LIFE.

15:23.756 --> 15:26.008
{\an4}EVERY TIME CAROL
LAYS WASTE TO YOU HACKET
BOYS

15:26.091 --> 15:27.468
I HAVE TO
PICK UP THE PIECES.

15:27.551 --> 15:29.011
{\an1}YOUR GOING TO THE PRUDENTIAL
BUILDING?

15:29.094 --> 15:30.804
JOE, CAROL IS NOT
GOING TO SHOW UP.

15:30.888 --> 15:33.891
{\an1}BRIAN'S GOING TO BE
LEFT THERE, DEVASTATED.

15:33.974 --> 15:35.517
{\an1}I DON'T THINK IT WILL BE THAT
BAD.

15:35.601 --> 15:37.144
{\an1}OH NO,REMEMBER HOW <i> YOU</i>
FELT

15:37.227 --> 15:39.229
WHEN SHE BROKE UP
WITH YOU?

15:39.313 --> 15:41.732
{\an3}YOU CRIED ON MY SHOULDER
FOR TWO WEEKS.

15:41.815 --> 15:44.902
MY SKIN IS STILL
A LITTLE PRUNEY.

15:44.985 --> 15:46.528
WANT SOME COMPANY?

15:46.612 --> 15:50.199
JOE, THAT'S VERY SWEET
OF YOU.

15:50.282 --> 15:53.535
{\an1}HEY, BRIAN WOULD DO
THE SAME FOR ME.

15:53.619 --> 15:55.829
WELL, I'LL GO ANYWAY.

15:55.913 --> 15:58.374
{\an4}HEY ROY,WE NEED A COUPLE OF
SEATS ON YOUR NEXT FLIGHT TO
BOSTON.

15:58.457 --> 16:00.000
GEE GUYS, I'M SOLD OUT.

16:00.084 --> 16:02.169
WHY DON'T YOU FLY
YOUR OWN PLANE?

16:02.252 --> 16:04.838
OH, THAT'S RIGHT--
SOMEONE STOLE IT.

16:04.922 --> 16:05.547
(<i> LAUGHING</i> )

16:05.631 --> 16:08.050
WHERE'S MY HEAD?

16:08.133 --> 16:09.176
COME ON.

16:09.259 --> 16:13.889
WE GOT OT GET ON THAT
FLIGHT,WHAT ARE WE GOING TO DO?

16:13.972 --> 16:18.477
JUST FOLLOW MY LEAD.

16:18.560 --> 16:22.064
(<i> WITH SOUTHERN ACCENT:</i> )
HI, I'M LUANN

16:22.147 --> 16:24.233
AND THIS IS
MY HUSBAND HERB.

16:24.316 --> 16:26.610
{\an4}LOOK, WE'LL BE SITTING
RIGHT BEHIND THEM ON THE
PLANE .

16:26.694 --> 16:28.654
ISN'T THAT GREAT?

16:28.737 --> 16:29.363
I HOPE Y'ALL
LIKE TO TALK.

16:29.446 --> 16:31.573
WE JUST <i> LOVE</i> TO TALK.

16:31.657 --> 16:32.908
YOU KNOW,
HERB'S IN INSURANCE

16:32.991 --> 16:36.537
AND I JUST FOUND THE LORD.

16:36.620 --> 16:39.790
AND THE LORD WANTS YOU
TO BUY MORE INSURANCE.

16:39.873 --> 16:41.417
YOU KNOW, EDWARD

16:41.500 --> 16:44.420
{\an5}I WOULDN'T MIND
ONE MORE NIGHT
ON THE ISLAND.

16:44.503 --> 16:53.095
{\an3}I'LL GO EXCHANGE
THE TICKETS.

16:53.178 --> 17:05.482
(<i> ELEVATOR DINGS</i> )

17:05.566 --> 17:07.859
HEY, KID, YOU STILL WAITING?

17:07.943 --> 17:08.736
{\an1}AFRAID SO.FRAID
SO.

17:08.819 --> 17:11.488
OH LISTEN NOW, DON'T WORRY.

17:11.571 --> 17:12.906
SHE'LL BE HERE.

17:12.990 --> 17:14.700
I KNOW ABOUT
THESE THINGS.

17:14.782 --> 17:15.951
THANKS.

17:16.034 --> 17:19.621
{\an1}YES, SIR, I'VE
SEEN IT ALL UP HERE.

17:19.704 --> 17:24.126
{\an1}THIS PLACE IS A NEVER-ENDING
PANORAMA OF HUMANITY--

17:24.209 --> 17:29.548
{\an1}THE HEARTACHE, THE JOY,
THE DRAMA, THE TEARS.

17:29.631 --> 17:33.886
{\an1}I'VE EVEN HAD TO USE THIS BABY
A COUPLE OF TIMES.

17:33.969 --> 17:35.012
REALLY?

17:35.095 --> 17:37.306
HOW LONG HAVE YOU
WORKED HERE?

17:37.389 --> 17:43.270
OH, I DON'T WORK HERE.

17:43.353 --> 17:45.814
(<i> ELEVATOR DINGS</i> )

17:45.898 --> 17:47.649
OH, BOY.

17:47.733 --> 17:50.652
OKAY LOOK JOE,I KNOW YOU'RE
UPSET THAT I TOOK THE PLANE

17:50.736 --> 17:52.821
{\an5}I KNOW THAT,BUT I JUST COULDN'T
LET THIS OPPORTUNITY TO SEE
CAROL,

17:52.905 --> 17:54.323
SLIP BY WITHOUT TRYING.

17:54.406 --> 17:56.658
{\an1}AND YOU'LL BE HAPPY TO KNOW
SHE NEVER SHOWED.

17:56.742 --> 17:57.951
SO IF YOU CAME TO GLOAT

17:58.035 --> 18:01.163
THEN YOU CAN GLOAT ALL YOU WANT
TO.

18:01.246 --> 18:02.998
{\an1}BRAIN WE DIDN'T COME HERE
TO GLOAT.

18:03.081 --> 18:05.000
{\an1}BUT HECK, AS LONG AS
WE'RE HERE...

18:05.083 --> 18:06.543
DON'T LISTEN TO HIM BRIAN.

18:06.627 --> 18:08.545
WE'RE HERE BECAUSE
WE CARE ABOUT YOU.

18:08.629 --> 18:11.548
THAT'S RIGHT,WE WERE REALLY
CONCERNED ABOUT YOU.

18:11.632 --> 18:16.178
{\an3}WELL JOE, EVERYTHING HAPPENED
THE WAY YOU CALLED IT.

18:16.261 --> 18:18.514
I JUST FEEL LOUSY.

18:18.597 --> 18:19.848
I JUST WANT
TO GO BACK.

18:19.932 --> 18:20.641
TO NANTUCKET?

18:20.724 --> 18:24.186
NO, TO THE WOMB.

18:24.269 --> 18:28.524
WELL, CAROL SHOULD BE TAKING OFF
FOR LONDON ABOUT NOW.

18:28.607 --> 18:30.192
BOY, SILLY ME.

18:30.275 --> 18:32.736
{\an1}YOU KNOW,I THOUGHT I WAS
IRRESISTIBLE.

18:32.820 --> 18:35.739
(<i> LAUGHS</i> )

18:35.823 --> 18:39.159
OH, SORRY.
REFLEX.

18:39.243 --> 18:40.953
YOU KNOW ONE THINGS I WANTED TO
KNOW,

18:41.036 --> 18:42.830
WHY DID YOU HAVE
TO MEET HER HERE?

18:42.913 --> 18:44.873
WHAT'S SO SPECIAL
ABOUT THIS PLACE?

18:44.957 --> 18:46.708
{\an1}THIS WAS WHERE WE HAD
OUR FIRST DATE.

18:46.792 --> 18:49.586
WELL IN CASE THE PRUDENTIAL
HAS SPECIAL MEANING FOR ME, TOO.

18:49.670 --> 18:51.004
OH YEAH WHY IS THAT?

18:51.088 --> 18:54.299
{\an5}WELL,YOUR FIRST DATE WITH CAROL
WAS THE SAME NIGHT SHE DUMPED
ME.

18:54.383 --> 18:56.468
{\an1}MAYBE LATER WE COULD
SWING BY THE MOVIE THEATRE

18:56.552 --> 18:59.680
{\an3}WHERE I WAITED ALL NIGHT
FOR CAROL TO SHOW UP.

18:59.763 --> 19:03.725
WELL THIS IS TURNING INTO
A LOSER'S TOUR OF BOSTON.

19:03.809 --> 19:06.270
WE COULD STOP BY
ONE OF MY OLD HAUNTS--

19:06.353 --> 19:09.940
THE SOUTH BAY FUDGE FACTORY.

19:10.023 --> 19:12.526
{\an1}YOU KNOW I WAS THEIR BEST
CUSTOMER.

19:12.609 --> 19:14.903
FOR CHRISTMAS THEY MADE
A LIFE-SIZED STATUE OF ME

19:14.987 --> 19:16.530
OUT OF TAFFY.

19:16.613 --> 19:19.700
ATE IT IN HALF AN HOUR.

19:19.783 --> 19:21.910
WELL, LET'S GO.

19:21.994 --> 19:23.412
(<i> ELEVATOR DINGS</i> )

19:23.495 --> 19:25.330
BRIAN?

19:25.414 --> 19:26.790
BRIAN HACKETT?

19:26.874 --> 19:28.876
YEAH?

19:28.959 --> 19:31.253
THESE ARE FOR YOU.

19:31.336 --> 19:33.213
WHAT'S GOING ON?

19:33.297 --> 19:35.924
SOME LADY NAMED CAROL
GAVE THEM TO ME.

19:36.008 --> 19:38.093
WOW, CAROL? REALLY?

19:38.176 --> 19:39.678
{\an1}SHE WAS RUNNING LATE
AT THE AIRPORT

19:39.761 --> 19:42.306
SO SHE GAVE ME $30
TO HIGHTAIL OVER HERE.

19:42.389 --> 19:45.100
SHE HAD A MESSAGE
FOR YOU, TOO.

19:45.183 --> 19:46.768
YOU WANT TO HEAR IT?

19:46.852 --> 19:49.104
YEAH, YEAH.

19:49.187 --> 19:52.441
{\an3}SHE SAID, "OUR TIME TOGETHER
WAS BEAUTIFUL.

19:52.524 --> 19:55.402
{\an3}I TREASURE
EVERY MOMENT WE SHARED""

19:55.485 --> 19:58.864
SHE SAY ANYTHING ELSE?

19:58.947 --> 19:59.948
"YOU'LL ALWAYS
BE SPECIAL TO ME.

20:00.032 --> 20:00.699
WOW REALLY?

20:02.826 --> 20:05.245
{\an3}"YOU ALWAYS
COULD MAKE ME LAUGH.

20:05.329 --> 20:09.791
EVERY TIME I THINK
OF YOU, I SMILE."

20:09.875 --> 20:11.251
YOU'RE JUST SAYING THAT.

20:11.335 --> 20:15.631
NO, I MEAN IT.

20:15.714 --> 20:17.257
DO YOU?

20:17.341 --> 20:21.470
WOULD I LIE TO YOU?

20:21.553 --> 20:23.055
EXCUSE ME...

20:23.138 --> 20:25.015
THIS IS KIND
OF PERSONAL.

20:25.098 --> 20:27.142
DO YOU MIND?

20:27.225 --> 20:28.977
SORRY.I'M SORRY.

20:29.061 --> 20:33.565
IT'S JUST THAT I USED TO
GO OUT WITH YOU, TOO.

20:33.649 --> 20:38.320
{\an1}IT'S OKAY,IT'S OKAY, REALLY.
THEY CAN STAY.

20:38.403 --> 20:40.781
{\an3}SHE ALSO MENTIONED
WANTING TO KISS YOU.

20:40.864 --> 20:42.866
WOW, REALLY?

20:42.950 --> 20:44.826
{\an1}YOU HAVE TO SHARE A LOT OF BIG
BUCKS FOR A KISS.

20:44.910 --> 20:46.954
NO, NO, NO, THAT'S OKAY.

20:47.037 --> 20:50.457
I'LL TAKE YOUR WORD FOR IT.

20:50.540 --> 20:52.167
IS THAT IT?

20:52.250 --> 20:55.629
"AS MUCH AS IT HURTS,
I HAVE TO MOVE ON."

20:55.712 --> 20:57.172
HMM.

20:57.255 --> 20:58.465
SHE SAID THAT, HUH?

20:58.548 --> 20:59.174
NO,<i> I</i> SAID THAT.

20:59.257 --> 21:01.468
I GOT TO GET BACK
TO MY CAB.

21:01.551 --> 21:03.887
OH.

21:03.971 --> 21:06.014
IS THERE MORE?

21:06.098 --> 21:13.021
WHAT? NO TIP?

21:13.105 --> 21:14.690
A BUCK?

21:14.773 --> 21:18.694
I THINK I KNOW WHY
CAROL LEFT YOU.

21:18.777 --> 21:24.866
{\an1}WELL WAIT-- YOU NEVER
EVEN TOLD ME YOUR NAME.

21:24.950 --> 21:27.536
LUTHER.

21:27.619 --> 21:28.870
LUTHER TALBOT.

21:28.954 --> 21:33.959
REMEMBER ME FONDLY.

21:34.042 --> 21:37.045
{\an1}WELL, BRIAN, AT LEAST
SHE WAS THINKING OF YOU.

21:37.129 --> 21:38.171
YOU HAVE THAT.

21:38.255 --> 21:39.214
YEAH.

21:39.298 --> 21:42.009
HEY, GUYS,
THE SKY'S CLEARING UP.

21:42.092 --> 21:44.011
YEAH, YOU CAN
SEE THE STARS.

21:44.094 --> 21:48.015
YEAH, LOOKS
SO PEACEFUL.

21:48.098 --> 21:50.726
{\an1}YUP, IT'S LIKE A
LARGE CLOUD

21:50.809 --> 21:52.728
HAS BEEN LIFTED
FROM ALL OUR LIVES.

21:52.811 --> 21:53.812
OF COURSE, IT IS.

21:53.895 --> 21:58.066
CAROL'S FINALLY GONE.

21:58.150 --> 21:59.735
IT'S OKAY, JOE,
YOU CAN SAY IT.

21:59.818 --> 22:02.738
MAYBE IT'S FOR THE BEST.

22:02.821 --> 22:06.950
(<i> ELEVATOR DINGS</i> )

22:07.034 --> 22:09.077
{\an5}-CAROL?
-CAROL?
-CAROL?
